        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Question :- A square bar of cross-section $20 \\times 20 \\text{mm}^2$. The square bar attached to 6 bolts. Calculate the diameter of bolt if the maximum stress in the bolt is $75 \\text{N/mm}^2$; and that in square base is $150 \\text{N/mm}^2$."
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "solution :- given!"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Area of cross-section of square = $20 \\times 20 = 400 \\text{mm}^2$"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "$P_{\\text{load}}$ = load on square = Load on 6 bolts"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Maximum stress on bolts = $75 \\text{N/mm}^2$"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Maximum stress on Square base = $150 \\text{N/mm}^2$"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Now,"
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "\\text{Stress on Square} = \\frac{P_{\\text{load}}}{\\text{Area of square}}",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "150 \\text{ N/mm}^2 = \\frac{P_{\\text{load}}}{400 \\text{ mm}^2}",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "P_{\\text{load}} = 150 \\times 400 \\text{ N}",
          "display": true
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Again,"
        },
        {
          "type": "math",
          "latex": "\\text{Stress on Bolts} = \\frac{P_{\\text{load}}}{\\text{Area of bolts}}",
          "display": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
